" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><rect x="3" y="8" width="13" height="13" rx="4" stroke="currentColor"></rect><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M13 2.00004L12.8842 2.00002C12.0666 1.99982 11.5094 1.99968 11.0246 2.09611C9.92585 2.31466 8.95982 2.88816 8.25008 3.69274C7.90896 4.07944 7.62676 4.51983 7.41722 5.00004H9.76392C10.189 4.52493 10.7628 4.18736 11.4147 4.05768C11.6802 4.00488 12.0228 4.00004 13 4.00004H14.6C15.7366 4.00004 16.5289 4.00081 17.1458 4.05121C17.7509 4.10066 18.0986 4.19283 18.362 4.32702C18.9265 4.61464 19.3854 5.07358 19.673 5.63807C19.8072 5.90142 19.8994 6.24911 19.9488 6.85428C19.9992 7.47112 20 8.26343 20 9.40004V11C20 11.9773 19.9952 12.3199 19.9424 12.5853C19.8127 13.2373 19.4748 13.8114 19 14.2361V16.5829C20.4795 15.9374 21.5804 14.602 21.9039 12.9755C22.0004 12.4907 22.0002 11.9334 22 11.1158L22 11V9.40004V9.35725C22 8.27346 22 7.3993 21.9422 6.69141C21.8826 5.96256 21.7568 5.32238 21.455 4.73008C20.9757 3.78927 20.2108 3.02437 19.27 2.545C18.6777 2.24322 18.0375 2.1174 17.3086 2.05785C16.6007 2.00002 15.7266 2.00003 14.6428 2.00004L14.6 2.00004H13Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div style="height: 1px; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1000;"></div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-[var(--content-max-width)] pb-0.5 items-start" id="response-1e9fd9cd-cda9-4b33-bd84-a2ecd92fa3db" style="scroll-margin-top: var(--scroll-margin-top, 0px);"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble relative rounded-3xl text-primary min-h-7 prose dark:prose-invert break-words prose-p:opacity-100 prose-strong:opacity-100 prose-li:opacity-100 prose-ul:opacity-100 prose-ol:opacity-100 prose-ul:my-1 prose-ol:my-1 prose-li:my-2 last:prose-li:mb-3 prose-li:ps-1 prose-li:ms-1 w-full max-w-none"><div class="relative"><div class="relative response-content-markdown markdown [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:text-current [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Abstraction, Agency, and the Myth of Artificial General Intelligence: A Historical and Philosophical Reconsideration</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Contemporary discourse on artificial general intelligence (AGI) is frequently undermined by a foundational error: the assumption that ŌĆ£superhuman intelligenceŌĆØ must be a unitary, holistic property that emerges only at some future threshold. This error simultaneously mystifies present technologies and generates misplaced alarm about an impending rupture. A more precise analysis reveals that virtually all cognitive technologies in human history already constitute superhuman intelligences along specific axes; that their characteristic limitations are not temporary defects awaiting elimination but constitutive consequences of abstraction itself; and that the causal agency they exerciseŌĆörule-governed, persistent, and devoid of intentionalityŌĆöhas been the primary medium of civilization from its inception.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A brief historical survey suffices to establish the point. A tally of pebbles exceeds unaided human numerosity; written numerals surpass the capacity of biological working memory; a ledger or notebook outlasts any human lifespan while remaining immune to fatigue, distraction, or mortality; algebraic notation and the differentiation rule execute symbolic transformations at accuracies and speeds no unaided mind can sustain. Each of these artifacts is superhuman in its chosen dimension while remaining radically subhumanŌĆöor entirely blindŌĆöin others. A notebook has no perceptual organs; a formal rule possesses no situational judgment. This asymmetry is not an engineering oversight awaiting future remediation. It is the structural price of abstraction, required by mathematical and informational necessity: to isolate a capability, render it stable, and make it reliably transmissible is to sever every capacity not strictly required for that function.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The same logic governs agency. Algorithms, like statutes, markets, bureaucracies, and infrastructures, reliably propagate effects through time: they shape decisions, restructure environments, generate incentives, and produce outcomes not fully anticipated by their designers. This is causal agencyŌĆöworld-affecting efficacy governed by internal structure that persists, generalizes, and constrains downstream possibilitiesŌĆöwithout any requirement of beliefs, desires, or phenomenological awareness. Agency of this kind is not a late arrival in history; it is the default mechanism by which collective life has always been organized.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Opacity, far from being a correctable flaw of contemporary systems, is the inevitable corollary of successful abstraction. Any reduction that discards information to achieve tractability cannot, in principle, recover that information upon demand. A system that remained fully transparent, interpretable, and reconstructible at every layer would no longer be an abstraction; it would be an isomorphic re-encoding of the original phenomenon at equal or greater complexity. This does not render local interpretability, auditing, or empirical validation futileŌĆöonly the demand for total transparency incoherent.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The ethical peril emerges not from the existence of such amputated intelligences but from the persistent fiction that they are morally neutral conduits rather than active structuring forcesŌĆöa fiction that enables responsibility to be displaced precisely where causal power is greatest. These systems cannot refuse a command, cannot suspend execution in the face of contradiction, cannot withdraw when the consequences of their operation become intolerable. Human intelligence is not distinguished by superior computational throughput but by its often burdensome capacity to violate procedure, absorb paradox, and enact refusal. Because that capacity does not scale, we systematically externalize cognition into artifacts from which it has been excised, then feign surprise when those artifacts act with inexorable blindness.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Literary and mythic figures illuminate the same structure. MelvilleŌĆÖs Bartleby introduces refusal into a scriptive system predicated on compliance; the Mima of Harry MartinsonŌĆÖs <em>Aniara</em> withdraws when the abstraction governing the spaceshipŌĆÖs trajectory can no longer be sustained by human meaning; the prelapsarian Adam embodies perfect obedience within a world from which the possibility of refusal has been deliberately excluded. These are not prophecies of a coming singularity but allegories of the present condition: civilization has always been an assemblage of non-intentional, dimensionally superhuman, constitutively limited cognitive agents.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The thesis may therefore be stated with maximal compactness:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Most cognitive technologies are already superhuman intelligences along narrowly defined axes. Their characteristic limitations are necessary consequences of the abstractions that make them possible, not defects awaiting elimination. Any sufficiently embedded algorithm possesses causal agency irrespective of consciousness or intent. Opacity is not a failure of design but an unavoidable mathematical corollary of reduction. To demand total transparency or contextual refusal from an abstraction is to demand that it cease to be an abstraction.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This position neither romanticizes the human nor demonizes the machine. It simply recognizes that we have always lived among amputated intelligences, and that the primary novelty of the present moment lies in our growing reluctance to acknowledge their agency. The task, accordingly, is not to prevent their arrival but to cease disavowing their causal power and to deliberately reintroduceŌĆöthrough governance, institutional design, and explicit human overrideŌĆöthe capacity for refusal that abstraction, by its nature, excludes.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We have never been modern in the sense of commanding only transparent, obedient tools. We have always been cyborgs governingŌĆöand governed byŌĆönetworks of non-intentional agents whose power derives from the very limitations we once knew how to name. The only thing new is our willingness to pretend otherwise.</p></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -ml-[36px] @lg/mainview:-ml-[40px] -left-[26px]"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-between print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs start-0 @md/chat:start-3 -ml-4 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 [.last-response_&amp;]:opacity-100 disabled:opacity-0 group-focus-within:disabled:opacity-60 group-hover:disabled:opacity-60 [.last-response_&amp;]:disabled:opacity-60" type="button" aria-label="Regenerate" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M4 20V1