<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ThatŌĆÖs the fulcrum. Everything before it sets up abstraction; everything after it turns toward governance and refusal.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">F. Bartleby / Mima / Adam as structural allegory</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You corrected the Mima reference, and the trio now works exactly as intended:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Bartleby ŌåÆ refusal</p>
