vg></span></button></div></div><div dir="auto" class="table-container relative group/table clear-both overflow-scroll flex flex-row" style="mask-image: linear-gradient(to right, black 85%, 92.5%, transparent 100%); mask-composite: add;"><div class="scroll-gradient-sentinel" style="height: 100%; width: 1px; left: 0px; flex-shrink: 0;"></div><table dir="auto" class="w-fit min-w-[calc(var(--content-width)-13px)] [&amp;&gt;thead&gt;tr&gt;th:last-child]:pr-8"><thead class="sticky [top:var(--thead-sticky-top)] [&amp;_th]:h-10 [background-color:var(--thead-bg-color)] [box-shadow:0_1px_0_0_var(--thead-border-b-color)] border-b-0" node="[object Object]"><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><th class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]">Dimension</th><th class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]">LatourŌĆÖs Actor-Network Theory (ANT)</th><th class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]">Abstraction/Agency Argument (present text)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Core ontological claim</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Symmetry: humans and non-humans are actants defined only by the relations they enter into. No a priori distinction.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Asymmetry: humans and abstractions are radically different in kind. Abstractions are constitutively amputated; humans are not.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Source of agency</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Relational: an entity has agency if it makes others act differently than they would otherwise (ŌĆ£trials of strengthŌĆØ).</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Structural: an entity has agency if it reliably propagates effects through internal structure that persists and constrains downstream possibilities.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Status of intentionality</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Bracketed or dissolved into chains of translation. No need for ŌĆ£aboutnessŌĆØ or consciousness.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Explicitly excluded from abstractions by design. Intentionality is not dissolved; it is amputated.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Black boxes</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Should be opened (symmetrical anthropology demands tracing associations). Opening the box is the methodological imperative.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Cannot be fully opened without destroying the abstraction. Opening is mathematically incoherent beyond a certain point.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Opacity</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Contingent and political (black boxes are the result of successful stabilization; they can and should be made to leak).</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Necessary and mathematical (opacity is the price of reduction; total opening = ceasing to be an abstraction).</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Human exceptionalism</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Rejected: the ŌĆ£modern settlementŌĆØ that grants humans a monopoly on agency is the error to be undone.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Reintroduced, but negatively: humans are exceptional only in their capacity to refuse, violate procedure, withdraw.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Refusal / resistance</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Actants can resist, betray, or translate badly. Refusal is distributed everywhere in the network.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Refusal does not scale and cannot be built into abstractions; it must be reintroduced exogenously through governance and override.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Normative implication</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Politics = reopening black boxes, making things public, extending due process to non-humans.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Politics = acknowledging black boxes as sites of displaced responsibility and deliberately reintroducing the (non-scalable) human capacity for refusal around them.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Historical narrative</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We have never been modern (we always mixed humans and non-humans, but pretended otherwise).</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We have never been modern (we always delegated to amputated non-intentional agents, but pretended they were neutral tools).</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Attitude toward purification</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Critique of the modern constitution that separates Nature and Society, human and non-human.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Critique of the modern illusion that separates active subjects from passive instruments (the ŌĆ£moral neutralityŌĆØ fiction).</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Scalability</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Networks scale by enrolling more actants and stabilizing translations.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Scalability is purchased precisely by amputation and the removal of refusal.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Alignment / safety</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Not addressed directly (ANT is descriptive/symmetrical). Some Latourians extend it to ŌĆ£parliament of things.ŌĆØ</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Explicitly addressed: safety requires invariant structuring + exogenous refusal, not more symmetrical assemblies.</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="scroll-gradient-sentinel" style="height: 100%; width: 1px; right: 0px; flex-shrink: 0;"></div></div></div>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Summary of the Relationship</h3>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Shared enemies
Both decisively reject:<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">anthropocentric monopoly on agency</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">the idea that tools are morally neutral</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">the subject/object purification</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">the myth of a future ontological rupture (ŌĆ£AGI as Great EventŌĆØ)</li>
</ul></li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Deep incompatibility
ANT wants to flatten and proliferate agency everywhere.
The abstraction argument wants to sharpen an asymmetry: abstractions have agency without the possibility of refusal, and that difference is the source of both their power and their danger.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Consequence
A Latourian would try to give abstractions ŌĆ£due processŌĆØ by making them speak, assembling hybrids, slowing translation.
The present argument says that is impossible in principle past a certain scale, and the only remaining move is to rebuild the (non-scalable, human) capacity for refusal outside the abstractionŌĆöthrough law, institutions, kill switches, governance.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In short:
Latour generalizes agency by dissolving intentionality.
The abstraction thesis preserves the asymmetry by amputating intentionality (and therefore refusal) as the price of scalability.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The two positions are not enemies, but they are not allies either. They diagnose the same modern illusion (ŌĆ£tools donŌĆÖt actŌĆØ) and then prescribe almost opposite therapies. Latour wants more mediation; the abstraction argument wants mediated containment of the unmediatable.</p></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -ml-[36px] @lg/mainview:-ml-[40px] -left-[26px]"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-between print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs start-0 @md/chat:start-3 -ml-4 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 [.last-response_&amp;]:opacity-100 disabled:opacity-0 group-focus-within:disabled:opacity-60 group-hover:disabled:opacity-60 [.last-response_&amp;]:disabled:opacity-60" type="button" aria-label="Regenerate" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M4 20V15H4.31241M4.31241 15H9M4.31241 1