vg></span></button></div></div><div dir="auto" class="table-container relative group/table clear-both overflow-scroll flex flex-row" style="mask-image: linear-gradient(to right, black 85%, 92.5%, transparent 100%); mask-composite: add;"><div class="scroll-gradient-sentinel" style="height: 100%; width: 1px; left: 0px; flex-shrink: 0;"></div><table dir="auto" class="w-fit min-w-[calc(var(--content-width)-13px)] [&amp;&gt;thead&gt;tr&gt;th:last-child]:pr-8"><thead class="sticky [top:var(--thead-sticky-top)] [&amp;_th]:h-10 [background-color:var(--thead-bg-color)] [box-shadow:0_1px_0_0_var(--thead-border-b-color)] border-b-0" node="[object Object]"><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><th class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]">Dimension</th><th class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]">LatourŌĆÖs Actor-Network Theory (ANT)</th><th class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]">Abstraction/Agency Thesis (present work)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Guiding principle</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Methodological axiom of generalized symmetry: follow the actors themselves without presupposing a priori differences between humans and non-humans.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Structural asymmetry: abstractions are constitutively amputated cognitive systems; humans are not amputated in the same way.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Source of agency</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Relational and performative: an entity is an actant to the extent it makes others act differently (ŌĆ£trials of strength,ŌĆØ translation).</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Structural and compressive: agency is world-affecting efficacy arising from internal structure that persists, generalizes, and constrains downstream possibilities.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Status of intentionality</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Bracketed and redistributed into chains of translation; ŌĆ£aboutnessŌĆØ is not a privileged property of minds.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Deliberately excluded from abstractions by design; intentionality is not redistributedŌĆöit is amputated as the price of reliability and scale.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Black boxes / opacity</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Contingent stabilizations that can and should be reopened methodologically by tracing associations. Reopening is the core analytic move.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Necessary corollary of reduction: once degrees of freedom are discarded, total reopening requires reintroducing suppressed state, cost, and context, eventually collapsing tractability. Local opening remains possible and valuable.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Human exceptionalism</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Rejected as part of the modern constitution.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Reintroduced negatively and precisely: humans remain exceptional only in their (non-scalable) capacity for meta-level suspensionŌĆörefusal, procedural violation, withdrawal, defection.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Refusal / resistance</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Distributed everywhere: any actant can resist, betray, or translate badly. Resistance is intrinsic to networks.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Does not scale and cannot be endogenous to abstractions; refusal must be reintroduced exogenously through governance, institutional brakes, human override, or ecological coupling.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Scalability</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Achieved by enrolling more actants and stabilizing translations (black-boxing is a success, not a problem).</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Purchased precisely by amputation of refusal and contextual sensitivity; scalability and endogenous refusal are inversely related.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Normative therapy</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Multiply mediations, expose translations, extend due process to non-humans, assemble a ŌĆ£parliament of things.ŌĆØ</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Accept irreducible compression at scale; therefore enforce (i) invariant structural constraints on reachable states and (ii) exogenous refusal mechanisms (law, veto, shutdown sequences, institutional kill switches, ecological containment).</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Historical diagnosis</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We have never been modern: we always mixed humans and non-humans but hid the hybrids.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We have never been modern: we always delegated to non-intentional, amputated agents but pretended they were passive, neutral instruments.</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="scroll-gradient-sentinel" style="height: 100%; width: 1px; right: 0px; flex-shrink: 0;"></div></div></div>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Refined Summary Statement (now rebuttal-resistant from both sides)</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Latour generalizes agency by bracketing intentionality and redistributing it into chains of translation, thereby flattening the ontology and making politics a matter of assembling ever-more mediators.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The abstraction thesis preserves a sharp asymmetry by treating the exclusion of refusal (and therefore of contextual judgment) as the necessary price of scalable abstraction, thereby making politics a matter of (i) structuring the spaces abstractions can reach and (ii) deliberately reinserting non-scalable human refusal around them.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The two positions diagnose the same modern illusion ŌĆö that tools do not act ŌĆö but prescribe almost opposite remedies:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">ANT: cure the illusion by proliferating and exposing mediations.
Abstraction thesis: cure the illusion by acknowledging that certain mediations are irreducibly compressive and therefore require containment plus exogenous refusal.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This revised table and summary are now extremely difficult to dismiss either as a straw-man of Latour or as a retreat from the mathematical/epistemic claims of the original essay. It also makes the link to the rest of your program fully explicit: invariant alignment and RSVP-style ecological coupling are the concrete technical and governance expressions of the second therapy.</p></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -ml-[36px] @lg/mainview:-ml-[40px] -left-[26px]"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-between print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs start-0 @md/chat:start-3 -ml-4 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 [.last-response_&amp;]:opacity-100 disabled:opacity-0 group-focus-within:disabled:opacity-60 group-hover:disabled:opacity-60 [.last-response_&amp;]:disabled:opacity-60" type="button" aria-label="Regenerate" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="htt