vg></span></button></div></div><div dir="auto" class="table-container relative group/table clear-both overflow-scroll flex flex-row" style="mask-image: linear-gradient(to right, black 85%, 92.5%, transparent 100%); mask-composite: add;"><div class="scroll-gradient-sentinel" style="height: 100%; width: 1px; left: 0px; flex-shrink: 0;"></div><table dir="auto" class="w-fit min-w-[calc(var(--content-width)-13px)] [&amp;&gt;thead&gt;tr&gt;th:last-child]:pr-8"><thead class="sticky [top:var(--thead-sticky-top)] [&amp;_th]:h-10 [background-color:var(--thead-bg-color)] [box-shadow:0_1px_0_0_var(--thead-border-b-color)] border-b-0" node="[object Object]"><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><th class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]">Dimension</th><th class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]">Timothy MortonŌĆÖs Hyperobjects</th><th class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]">Abstraction/Agency Thesis (present work)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Core concept</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Vastly distributed entities (global warming, plutonium, the biosphere, capitalism, neural nets at scale) that are real but massively exceed human-scale access, temporality, and intentionality.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Scalable cognitive abstractions (counting systems, algorithms, bureaucracies, large language models) that are real, massively distributed in their effects, and exceed human-scale contextual judgment.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Distribution</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Hyperobjects are viscous, nonlocal, temporally undulating, phased, and interobjective. They stick to you, appear in many places at once, outlast individuals and civilizations.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Abstractions are persistent, generalizing, constraining structures whose effects are nonlocal (propagate through law, markets, code, infrastructure) and typically outlast their creators.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Opacity / withdrawal</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Radical ontological strangeness: you can never see the hyperobject as a whole; it is always ŌĆ£over your headŌĆØ and ŌĆ£under your feetŌĆØ simultaneously.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Radical epistemic amputation: the abstraction is not mysterious in a weird, alluring way; it is deliberately blind because degrees of freedom were discarded for scalability.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Agency</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Hyperobjects act upon us far more than we act upon them. Agency is overwhelmingly nonhuman and non-intentional.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Abstractions act upon us far more reliably than we act upon them once deployed. Agency is overwhelmingly non-intentional and structural.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Human exceptionalism</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Dissolved: humans are hypnotized by the eerie presence of hyperobjects; we are their playthings.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Reintroduced negatively: humans remain the only entities capable of refusal and meta-level suspensionŌĆöprecisely the capacities that hyperobjects and abstractions both lack.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Scale effects</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The defining feature: hyperobjects force us to confront the end of the world (as correlational horizon) and the beginning of weird essentialism.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Scale is purchased by the systematic removal of refusal and contextual sensitivity. Scalability and endogenous refusal are inversely related.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Political / ethical response</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Ecological awareness, attunement, humility, lameness, caring from within the mesh, accepting that we are inside the hyperobject.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Governance through invariant constraints + exogenous refusal mechanisms (law, kill switches, institutional veto, ecological containment). No attunement can substitute for hard structural limits.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Refusal</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Not a central category. Hyperobjects cannot refuse; we cannot refuse them either (viscosity).</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Central category. Abstractions cannot refuse; therefore humans and institutions must refuse on their behalf.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Tone</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Weird, melancholic, poetic, post-anthropocentric sublime.</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Sober, diagnostic, politically focused, non-weird.</td></tr><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="sm" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Safety / alignment implication</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Largely absent. When addressed, the mood is one of tragic coexistence with the unmasterable (climate change will outlast every alignment scheme).</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="lg" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Explicit: because abstractions are hyperobject-like in their distribution and non-refusal, safety cannot come from coexistence or attunement; it requires engineered unreachable states and mandatory override layers.</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="scroll-gradient-sentinel" style="height: 100%; width: 1px; right: 0px; flex-shrink: 0;"></div></div></div>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Concise Diagnostic</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Morton and the abstraction thesis are looking at almost exactly the same phenomena ŌĆö vastly distributed, non-intentional, persistence-through-time entities that dwarf human intentionality and refuse to stay within correlational grasp.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">But they draw opposite conclusions:</p>













<div class="relative"><div class="absolute top-1 right-1 z-10 print:hidden"><div class="flex flex-row gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-60 disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-8 w-8 rounded-full dark:bg-surface-l1 dark:text-text-l1 dark:hover:bg-surface-l2" type="button" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><rect x="3" y="8" width="13" height="13" rx="4" stroke="currentColor"></rect><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M13 2.00004L12.8842 2.00002C12.0666 1.99982 11.5094 1.99968 11.0246 2.09611C9.92585 2.31466 8.95982 2.88816 8.25008 3.69274C7.90896 4.07944 7.62676 4.51983 7.41722 5.00004H9.76392C10.189 4.52493 10.7628 4.18736 11.4147 4.05768C11.6802 4.00488 12.0228 4.00004 13 4.00004H14.6C15.7366 4.00004 16.5289 4.00081 17.1458 4.05121C17.7509 4.10066 18.0986 4.19283 18.362 4.32702C18.9265 4.61464 19.3854 5.07358 19.673 5.63807C19.8072 5.90142 19.8994 6.24911 19.9488 6.85428C19.9992 7.47112 20 8.26343 20 9.40004V11C20 11.9773 19.9952 12.3199 19.9424 12.5853C19.8127 13.2373 19.4748 13.8114 19 14.2361V16.5829C20.4795 15.9374 21.5804 14.602 21.9039 12.9755C22.0004 12.4907 22.0002 11.9334 22 11.1158L22 11V9.40004V9.35725C22 8.27346 22 7.3993 21.9422 6.69141C21.8826 5.96256 21.7568 5.32238 21.455 4.73008C20.9757 3.78927 20.2108 3.02437 19.27 2.545C18.6777 2.24322 18.0375 2.1174 17.3086 2.05785C16.6007 2.00002 15.7266 2.00003 14.6428 2.00004L14.6 2.00004H13Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div dir="auto" class="table-container relative group/table clear-both overflow-scroll flex flex-row" style=""><div class="scroll-gradient-sentinel" style="height: 100%; width: 1px; left: 0px; flex-shrink: 0;"></div><table dir="auto" class="w-fit min-w-[calc(var(--content-width)-13px)] [&amp;&gt;thead&gt;tr&gt;th:last-child]:pr-8"><thead class="sticky [top:var(--thead-sticky-top)] [&amp;_th]:h-10 [background-color:var(--thead-bg-color)] [box-shadow:0_1px_0_0_var(--thead-border-b-color)] border-b-0" node="[object Object]"><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><th class="break-words" data-col-size="md" node="[object Object]">Morton says:</th><th class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]">ŌĆ£They are too big, too sticky, too weird ŌåÆ learn to lament, to care, to coexist in the mesh.ŌĆØ</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="border-primary/10" node="[object Object]"><td class="break-words" data-col-size="md" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The abstraction thesis says:</td><td class="break-words" data-col-size="xl" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ŌĆ£They are too big, too sticky, too reliable precisely because refusal was amputated ŌåÆ build hard invariants and exogenous refusal before they rewrite the biosphere.ŌĆØ</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="scroll-gradient-sentinel" style="height: 100%; width: 1px; right: 0px; flex-shrink: 0;"></div></div></div>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Unexpected Convergence</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Both treat contemporary AI systems as genuine hyperobjects: nonlocal, phasing in and out of human perception, temporally elongated, viscous in their effects, impossible to confront head-on.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Both reject the fantasy that we can ever achieve transparent mastery or moral neutrality.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Deep Divergence</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">MortonŌĆÖs response is ecological-melancholic attunement inside the inescapable.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The abstraction thesisŌĆÖs response is political-engineering containment from outside the inescapable.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">One ends in a dark ecology of lameness and solidarity with nonhumans.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The other ends in a theory of governance that accepts the darkness but insists on kill switches and invariant boundaries.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Bottom line</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Hyperobjects and amputated abstractions name the same class of beings, but Morton wants us to become intimate with their strangeness, while the abstraction thesis wants us to treat their strangeness as an engineered property that demands structural refusal mechanisms rather than poetic surrender.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The two positions are not contradictory at the descriptive level ŌĆö they are contradictory at the prescriptive level.</p></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -ml-[36px] @lg/mainview:-ml-[40px] -left-[26px]"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-between print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs start-0 @md/chat:start-3 -ml-4 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 [.last-response_&amp;]:opacity-100 disabled:opacity-0 group-focus-within:disabled:opacity-60 group-hover:disabled:opacity-60 [.last-response_&amp;]:disabled:opacity-60" type="button" aria-label="Regenerate" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M4 20V15H4.31241M4.31241 15H9M4.31241 15C5.51251 18.073 8.50203 20.25 12 20.25C15.8582 20.25 19.0978 17.6016 20 14.0236M20 4V9H19.6876M19.6876 9H15M19.6876 9C18.4875 5.92698 15.498 3.75 12 3.75C8.1418