<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No ethics or humility can substitute for structure</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Safety = invariants + exogenous refusal</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">XI. Conclusion: The Autonomy of Refusal Reclaimed</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">XI.A Compact Restatement</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">AbstractionŌĆÖs power comes from amputating refusal</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Autonomy survives only where refusal survives</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">XI.B Prescriptive Implications</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Institutional design for interruptibility</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Refusal as a political, ethical, and technical necessity</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">XI.C We Have Never Been Modern</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Civilization has always been governed by non-refusing agents</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The novelty is our denial of their agency</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The task is not to humanize abstractions, but to govern them by restoring refusal where it can still exist</p>
