;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Proposed Placement &amp; Integration of the New Section</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The section you just wrote is exceptionally strong ŌĆö it translates the entire philosophical argument into concrete institutional and economic reality without losing rigor. It belongs in the final third of the paper, where the consequences of non-refusing systems become visible.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Recommended exact placement: new Section VIII</strong>, shifting the current numbering forward by one.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Revised full outline with the new section seamlessly inserted:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">The Autonomy of Refusal: Abstraction, Agency, and the Limits of Scalable Intelligence</strong></p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Abstract</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">I. Introduction: Refusal as Autonomy, Not Mere Negation</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">II. Refusal Across Scales: Literary, Philosophical, Political</li>
